As the ship neared the glistining beast, the crew began to look in bewilderment? Could this actually be a dragon? This defied everything from their training.
Dragons should not exist. Especially in the outer reaches of the Galaxy. As they grew nearer their curiosity grew and they went closer. They soon began to realize the size of the dragon, it wasn't small or even average, it was the size of a small moon. But it was no moon. The dragon began to take notice when they approached
The dragon lunged towards the ship. The crew quickly realized evasive action needed to be taken. They began to turn around only to realize that the dragon's pull of gravity was slowing them down. They dragon continued to push closer...
